name: Drops in the rainforest #2
description:
The sun was scorching the rainforest for a long time and finally the rain came - for almost a week! These drops are a sign of refreshment and restoration to the land.

To feel the photo: Countryside, noises of the family gathered nearby, it's morning, a chilly weather for Brazilian standards, a slow chilly breeze flowing once in a while.

About the plants: Mainly Mimosa Pudica aka touch-me-not or sleepy plant
Equipment: Sony Alpha A6500 + Sony E 18-135mm F/3.5-5.6 OSS
Location: Sapucaia, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil
